      "term" : "dialysis-related amyloidosis",
      "definition" : "means beta2-microglobulin amyloidosis\nsecondary to long-term haemodialysis or continuous ambulatory peritoneal\ndialysis"
    } ]
  }, {
    "paragraph" : "6(e)",
    "text" : "regularly using the upper limbs for weight-bearing for a continuous\r\nperiod of at least the one year before the clinical onset of rotator cuff\r\nsyndrome; or\r\nNote: Examples of situations in which the upper limbs may regularly be used for weight-\r\nbearing include transfers from a wheelchair to a chair or bed, and the use of crutches or other\r\nwalking aids",
    "definedTerms" : [ ]
  }, {
    "paragraph" : "6(f)",
    "text" : "having anatomical narrowing of the subacromial space on the affected\r\nside at the time of the clinical onset of rotator cuff syndrome",
    "definedTerms" : [ {
      "term" : "anatomical narrowing of the subacromial space",
      "definition" : "means an acquired\nreduction in the space between the acromion and the upper end of the\nhumerus. Causes would include:\n(a) malunited fractures of the acromion, clavicle or greater tuberosity;\n(b) osteophytes or tumours projecting into the subacromial space; or\n(c) sutures, pins or wires from previous surgery"
    } ]
  }, {
    "paragraph" : "6(g)",
